\u2014^\u2014\nLouis D. Blauvelt. 63. Colorado\nstate highway engineer, who as r\nwar time army major planned and\nbuilt a $40,000,000 toxic gas plant J\nat Edgewater arsenal In Maryland,\ndied here yesterday.\nAUTO ACCIDENT\nSTRAWN, Tex., Oct. 27\u2014(IPs\u2014 s\nJulius Schwasig and Leonce Rieu,\n21, both of Strawn, were instantly\nkilled yesterday when a light car j\ntn which they were riding collided i\nwith two other automobiles on the I\nhighway near here, and overturned.\nThree occupants of one of the other\ncars were slightly injured and were c\ntreated at a Ranger hospital. 1\nSchwasig and Rieu, according tc f\nreports, were attempting tn pass\nanother car occupied by Mrs. and\nMrs. C. F. Waldrop and Mr. and\nMrs. H L. McKay, all of Marshal!.\nThe light car struck the rear of\nthe Marshall car. then crashed in\nto a machine driven bv L. J. Heff\nner, who lives in California.\nRITES FOR EDITOR\nFORT WORTH, Oct. 27\u2014<*>>\u2014\nFuneral rites were set for this\nafternoon for Ned C. Record. 29.\nsports editor of the Record-Tele\ngram since 1925. He died Seturdav\nat 5:40 p. m. of penumonia that\nfollowed an emergency operation t\nOct. 16 for appendicitis.\nFellow employes on the Star\nTelegram and Record-Telegram ex\npected to serve as pallbarers at the\nservices at 3:30 p. m. from St MarW\nCatholic church.\n_\nLUFKIN KILLING\nLUFKIN. Oct. 27\u2014<&)\u2014Tom Mur- I\nray, 30, Jitney owner, was shot and\nkilled here yesterday on a down-\ntown street. A meat cutter, resid\ning at Jasper and formerly of\nLufkin, surrendered to the sheriff.\nInsull Is Purchaser\nOf Valley Orchard\nMartin J. Insull, the multi-mil\nj iionaire who. in company with\nI other men of wealth, visited the\nValley recently, was so impressed\nwith this section that he has\nbought a 12-acre citrus orchard as\nan investment and an experiment\nit was announced Monday.\nMr. Insull and a partv of about\n30 men inspected the Rio Grande\nValley from Mission to Port Isabel\nwhile here, and although the\nweather was inclement during their\nvisit, they appreciated conditions\nhere and realized the brilliant fu\nture to such an extent that the\nleader decided to purchase an or\nchard. it was said today. It was\nfurther added that others of the\nparty may follow Mr. Insull and\nbuy orchards for development.\nSubstitute Mother i\nIs Not Wanted\nSubstitute mother wouldn t un\nderstand you. No mother equals\nyour own. So with your old tried\nj and true remedy for constipated,\nj torpid liver, there is no substitute.\nCarter's Little Liver Pills, made of\ni genuine vegetable calomel, is old\nest liver remedy known. Take Car\nter's. enjoy free flowing bile for\nthorough system cleansing. Red\nbottles only. Take Carter's. Adv.\nBEWARE THE COUGH FROM\nCOLDS THAT HANG ON\nCoughs from colds may lead to ee\u00bb\nnous trouble. You can stop them\nnow with Creomulsion. an emulsified\ncreosote that is pleasant to take.\nCreomulsion is a medical discovery\nwith two-fold action; it soothes and\nheals the inflamed membranes and in\nhibits germ growth.\nOf all known drugs creosote is rec\nognised by high medical authoritiea\nas one of the greatest healing agencies\nfor Roughs from colds and bronchial\nirritation*. Creomulsion contains, in\naddition to creosote, other healme\nelements which soothe and heal the\ninflamed membranes and atop the ir\nritation, while the creosote goes on to\nthe stomach, it absorbed into the\nblood, attacks the seat of the trouble\nand checks the growth of the germs.\nCrenmulsion is guaranteed satisfac\ntory in the treatment of coughs from\ncolds, bronchitis and minor forma of\nbronchial irritations, and is excellent\nfor building up the system after colda\nor flu. ^ney refunded if not re\nlieved after taking according to direc\ntion- Ask vnur ilniri'il tartvl\nCREOMULSION\nFOR THE COUGH FROM COLDS THAT HANG ON\nFuneral Services\nFor Rio Hondo Child\n(Special to The Herald)\nHARLINGEN, Oct. 27.\u2014Funeral\nsendees for Joseph Harry Brannon\nseven-.months old son of 'tr. and\nMrs. L. M. Brannon, of Rio Hondo,\nare to be held Monday afternoon\nat Thompson\u2019s chapel, with the\nRev. C. H. Harrison, pastor th*\nChristian church here officiating\nInterment will be in the Mont Metp\ncemetery. The child Is survived by\nhis parents, one brother and two\nsisters.\nNinety-two Bodies\nTaken From Mine\nSMYRNA. Asia Minor. Oct. 27\n(A*)\u2014Torrenttal rains in Smyrna\nhave brought death to 30 persons\nand destroyed 220 houses. All elec\ntricity has been cut off by the\nseething torrents, which have raced\ndown the street*, carrying horses\nand carriages toward the sea.\nThe governor, attempting to or\nganize rescue work, was almost\ncarried into the sea from his auto\nmobile.\nVannie Tilden\nI\nHome Baking\nSomething Different\n-IN\nDelicious Home Baked\nPastry and Bread\nPhone 753\n509 Elizabeth Brownsville\nUnderstanding\nWhen our customers bring their fi\nnancial problems to the Merchants'\nNational, we try to put ourselves\n\u201cin their shoes.\u201d\nWe sincerely endeavor to consider\neach transaction from the other fel\nlow\u2019s point-of-view.\nCapital Stock:\nOriginally paid in $100,000.00\nIncreased from earnings 150,000.00 $250,000.00\nSurplus Fund, earned 275,000.00\nMERCHANTS'\nNATIONAL BANK\nB R. O W N S VlLLE TEXAS.*\n*m- rj|f*p 111111 -.'X*'\u2022' ^V,\nONE WILL ALWAYS ST A'\\N D OUT\n\n\nf\nI\n\n\nMiWer. and f\nbetter taste\n1032-36 Elizabeth St. Brownsville, Texas\nBe Ready ior That First Cold Night!\n\nWinter Bedding\nat Substantial Savings!\nAll wool blankets in fast colors\nSize 66x80\nPrice $5.90\nI t ine All-Woo!\nBlock Plaids; All Vir\nIgin Wool; Large Size,\n70x80 II11\nBlock Plaid\nBlankets\nExtra large afxe. 72x84 inched'\n\u00bbf fin* China cotton and oirgia\nWool; sateen bound. Wt. 5 lbs\n$3*98 p*lr\nCo tton-a nd-Wool\nBlankets\nSelected China cotton mixed\nwith small percentage af virgin\nwool; block plaids; sateen\nbound; 70x80 inches.\n$2.98 pale\nPlaid Cattail\nBlankets\nOutstanding 